                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d486">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">891.6363/10–1044: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Iran</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Morris</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Tehran</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1944-10-10T18:00:00+03:25"
                            >October 10, 1944—6 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/> [Received October 11—9:40 a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>749. ReEmbstel No. 744, October 9. Prime Minister confirmed to me last night that
                    oil concession negotiations had been postponed until after war. He further
                    stated he was immediately informing Soviet representatives here as well as
                    representatives of American and British oil companies now in Tehran of this
                    postponement.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Morris</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
